{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":216233,"duration_api_ms":214216,"num_turns":20,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6616c543-f23b-4fa5-bd9c-bd5fefb2f88b","total_cost_usd":0.89976625,"usage":{"input_tokens":14,"cache_creation_input_tokens":55173,"cache_read_input_tokens":618580,"output_tokens":9823,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":55173,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":14,"outputTokens":9823,"cacheReadInputTokens":618580,"cacheCreationInputTokens":55173,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.89976625,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed all three changed files (model.rs, service.rs, fs.rs). The changes make milestone_id a required String, remove all legacy backward-compatibility code (parse_legacy, backfill-on-read, canonicalize_entry_for_write), tighten find_matching_running_task_run to require started_at match, and remove the \"same bead already active\" guard in favor of started_at-based disambiguation. All 305 tests pass. The changes are well-structured and internally consistent, with one correctness gap around orphaned running entries.","amendments":[{"body":"In `record_task_run_start` (fs.rs ~line 2770-2797), when `find_matching_running_task_run` returns None but there IS exactly one matching running entry (len==1, different started_at), a new running entry is appended without finalizing the old one. This creates two open runless entries for the same bead/project. Subsequently calling `update_task_run` with `run_id=None` will hit the `open_matches.len() > 1` branch and fail with 'ambiguous task run update'. The test `runless_retry_with_new_started_at_appends_new_attempt` validates the start behavior but does not test that the resulting state is completable. Either: (a) auto-fail the old running entry when creating a new attempt (set outcome=Failed, finished_at=started_at of new attempt), or (b) add started_at as a disambiguator to update_task_run, or (c) add a test proving that callers are expected to always supply run_id when multiple attempts exist and document this constraint.","rationale":"Without this fix, a legitimate retry scenario (same bead, no run_id, different started_at) creates a state where neither attempt can be finalized via the existing update_task_run API, which violates the acceptance criterion 'Controller can update linkage after each run outcome'."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"75e9eb0b-6618-428f-9f78-2cf37e572897"}
